<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-21T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-21T14:00:00-05:00" n="512" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d512">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">300.115/14287: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul General at London</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Skinner</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-21T15:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">September
                                            21, 1918—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>Consult Embassy regarding its No. 1418, August 27, 5 p.m. Take matter
                                up with Procurator General at once, and ascertain what proofs he
                                required in addition to those already presented to establish
                                American ownership of goods not sold and whether speedy
                                determination of questions of title may be expected, with a view to
                                effecting delivery of goods to American owners at earliest possible
                                moment.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>